            <div class="col-md-4">
                <h4 class="my-4">Other Aquatic Wildlife</h4>
                <p>VGDS hosts a rich diversity of aquatic wildlife, including:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Indian Smooth-Coated Otter</b> (Lutrogale perspicillata)</li>
                    <li><b>Gharial</b> (Gavialis gangeticus)</li>
                    <li><b>Freshwater Turtles:</b> Key species include the Indian Softshell Turtle (Nilsonia gangetica), Indian Peacock Softshell Turtle (Nilsonia hurum), Indian Roofed Turtle (Pangshura tecta), Indian Tent Turtle (Pangshura tentoria), Indian Flapshell Turtle (Lissemys punctata), and Indian Narrow-headed Softshell Turtle (Chitra indica).</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

            <div class="col-md-4">
                <br />
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Fish Species:</b> The sanctuary's waters are home to various fish species, such as the Helicopter Catfish (Wallago attu), Indian River Shad (Salmostoma bacalia), and Gangetic Mystus (Mystus cavasius).</li>
                </ul>
                <h4 class="my-4">Avifauna</h4>
                <p>VGDS is an Important Bird Area, supporting approximately 198 avifauna species, including:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li><b>Raptors:</b> Black Kite, Black-winged Kite, Shikra, Crested Serpent Eagle, and several vulnerable species such as the Eastern Imperial Eagle and Pallas's Fish Eagle.</li>
                    <li><b>Waterfowl and Waders:</b> The sanctuary provides habitat for a diverse range of waterfowl, including threatened species like the Indian Skimmer (Rynchops albicollis) and Greater Adjutant (Leptoptilos dubius).</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

